subSubSection.paragraph:
SEM observations
:— 

(
Figs 63–64
):

Externally, the striae are composed of 2–4 transapically elongated areolae becoming larger towards the margins. Rarely some of the areolae of the inner row are almost rounded (
Fig. 63
). One row of rounded areolae, interrupted at the valve poles, is present on the valve mantle. The external isolated pore opening is transapically elongated. The external proximal raphe endings are slightly expanded and are shortly bent away from the isolated pore. The distal fissures are short and terminate just below the last striae, bent to the same direction as the proximal raphe endings. Internally (
Fig. 64
), the central nodule is thickened. The raphe is straight and terminates onto small helictoglossae at the poles. The internal isolated pore opening is rounded and covered by an almost circular silica flap. The areolae are covered by hymenes and form a continuous strip over the striae.
